1️⃣ IdentityAttribute kya hai?
👉 IdentityAttribute = user (Identity) ka ek single attribute / property
Matlab:-
Identity = pura user object
IdentityAttribute = uske andar ka ek field
✅ Example:-
Agar ek user hai:-
Name: Rahul
Email: rahul@gmail.com
Department: IT
Manager: Amit
➡ Ye sab alag-alag IdentityAttribute hain.

🔹 2️⃣ Ye kya karta hai?
👉 Ye user ke attributes ko store aur manage karta hai
user ka data hold karta hai
workflows aur policies me use hota hai
provisioning aur access decisions me use hota hai.

🔹 3️⃣ Kya ye DB me save hota hai?
✅ Haan bhai, DB me store hota hai
Kaise?
Identity object DB me save hota hai
Uske andar attributes bhi store hote hain.

🔹 4️⃣ IdentityAttribute ke andar kya hota hai?
👉 Basically key-value pair + metadata:-
Field	             Meaning
name:-------Attribute ka naam (email, department)
value:------Uska value (rahul@gmail.com
, IT)
type:-------String / Boolean / Number
readOnly:---Change kar sakte ho ya nahi
required:---Mandatory hai ya nahi

